{
  "texts": [
    "Thus, future research should contemplate adapting their evaluation methods to incorporate the presence of MBU vulnerabilities.R5 -Evaluate SVD on MBU Vulnerabilities.",
    "The majority of studies on function-level VD [25,34,64] have typically assessed performance based on the number of correctly detected vulnerable functions.",
    "However, it is important to note that a single vulnerability might encompass multiple vulnerable functions.",
    "Therefore, merely identifying one vulnerable function does not necessarily equate to the comprehensive detection of the entire vulnerability.",
    "Acknowledging this, Sejfia et al. [193] emphasized the need for future research to account for the scenario of Multiple Base Unit (MBU) vulnerabilities during the training and testing phases of DL-based VD."
  ]
}